# Secrets manifest — {{CONSUMER_NAME}}

This file enumerates every secret this consumer reads at deploy or
test time, plus where it comes from and how often it rotates.

| Secret | Purpose | Source | Rotation |
|--------|---------|--------|----------|
| `NPM_TOKEN` | `npm install` from GitHub Packages (`@simodelne/pgas-*`) | Fine-grained PAT, `read:packages` on `simodelne` org | Quarterly |
| `PGAS_PROVIDER` | Default LLM provider name (e.g. `ollama`, `gemini`, `openai`) | `.env` | n/a (config, not a secret) |
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | (Optional) Google Gemini API key when `PGAS_PROVIDER=gemini` | `.env.local` for dev; GH Actions secret for CI | Per-incident |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | (Optional) OpenAI API key when `PGAS_PROVIDER=openai` | `.env.local` for dev; GH Actions secret for CI | Per-incident |

## Auth secrets

Auth mode is selected at startup via `PGAS_AUTH_MODE`
(`dev-static-token` | `magic-link`). Each mode has its own required
secret(s). See `server/auth/` and `.env.example` for the full env-var
surface; this section lists only the secret-bearing entries.

| Secret | Purpose | Required when | Source | Rotation |
|--------|---------|---------------|--------|----------|
| `PGAS_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 signing key for JWTs issued by the magic-link flow | `PGAS_AUTH_MODE=magic-link` | `openssl rand -hex 32`; `.env.local` for dev; GH Actions secret for prod | Rotating invalidates EVERY outstanding JWT — clients must re-authenticate |
| `PGAS_DEV_STATIC_TOKEN` | Single shared bearer token for the dev-static-token mode | `PGAS_AUTH_MODE=dev-static-token` | Any high-entropy string (`openssl rand -hex 32` recommended); `.env.local` for dev only | Rotating invalidates the single dev token — every dev/CI consumer must update |
| `<email-provider key>` | (Future) Email-send for magic-link delivery — plugin v0.1 logs to console only. Wire your provider via `authConfig.onMagicLink` in `server/auth/config.ts`. | Production with `PGAS_AUTH_MODE=magic-link` | Provider console; `.env.local` for dev; GH Actions secret for prod | Per provider policy (typically per-incident) |

**NEVER COMMIT** any of these values. They belong in `.env.local`
(gitignored) for development and in GitHub Actions secrets for CI / prod.
The `.gitignore` already excludes `.env*` except `.env.example`; double-
check before any push that no real values leaked in.

### Auth-secret rotation specifics

- **`PGAS_JWT_SECRET`**: rotating immediately invalidates every JWT the
  middleware will accept (signature check fails). Plan for client re-auth.
  For zero-downtime rotation, ship a brief overlap window with a
  before-and-after-key check — out of scope for v0.1.
- **`PGAS_DEV_STATIC_TOKEN`**: rotating invalidates the dev token; every
  dev/CI consumer that hits `/api/*` must update its `Authorization: Bearer`
  header. There is no overlap window — the env var holds one value.
- **`<email-provider key>`**: rotate per the provider's guidance. The
  `onMagicLink` callback in `server/auth/config.ts` is the seam to update.

## Rotation procedure

1. Generate a new value at the source (GitHub PAT settings / provider console).
2. Update `.env.local` for local dev.
3. `gh secret set <NAME>` for GH Actions.
4. Redeploy any running services.
5. Revoke the old value at the source.

## Anti-patterns

- DO NOT commit `.env.local` or any `*.env*` file other than `.env.example`.
- DO NOT log secret values, even at debug level. Use `[REDACTED]` placeholders.
- DO NOT echo secrets into the GitHub Actions log. Use `add-mask` when echoing is unavoidable.

## Audit

Once per quarter, the orchestrator runs:

```bash
git log --all --full-history -p | grep -iE '(api_key|secret|token|password)\s*[=:]' | head -50
```

Any genuine leak triggers a hot-fix rotation per HANDOVER's hot-fix
protocol (see `simodelne/pgas`/HANDOVER.md).
